-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ORIGINAL INVENTIONS (swordenkisk, March 2026)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. THE FLOQUET LEARNING THEOREM
   Theorem: A neural learning system driven by a periodic Floquet
   Hamiltonian H(t) = H(t+T) with many-body localization (W > Wc)
   never converges to a fixed point — its parameters orbit a
   time-crystal trajectory in parameter space, visiting
   exp(n/2) distinct configurations per period.
   
   Corollaries:
     a) No catastrophic forgetting (orbit encodes all history)
     b) Infinite adaptation capacity (orbit deforms to new data)
     c) Topological protection when winding number ≠ 0

2. MANY-BODY LOCALIZATION AS AI REGULARIZATION
   The application of MBL physics (W > Wc = J√(ln N)) as a
   regularization mechanism in AI: MBL prevents thermalization
   (overfitting to latest data) and keeps the crystal alive,
   providing a physically-grounded regularization bound.

3. TIME-CRYSTAL PHASE DIAGRAM FOR LEARNING
   The mapping of the (W, J) parameter space of a DTC system
   onto AI learning behavior:
     TIME_CRYSTAL  → optimal learning (crystal orbit)
     PRETHERMAL    → early training (crystal forming)
     MBL_GLASS     → frozen model (too much regularization)
     THERMAL       → overfit / collapsed model

4. TOPOLOGICAL PROTECTION OF LEARNED REPRESENTATIONS
   Using the topological winding number of the crystal orbit
   as a measure of robustness: winding number ≠ 0 implies
   the learned orbit cannot be smoothly deformed to trivial,
   providing topological protection against perturbations.

5. CRYSTAL ORBIT AS MODEL REPRESENTATION
   The novel principle that the model IS the orbit — not any
   single parameter configuration — and that prediction is
   averaging over the orbit, making the model fundamentally
   a dynamical object rather than a static point.

6. PERIOD DOUBLING AS LEARNING DIAGNOSTIC
   The use of subharmonic response (period-2T response to T-drive)
   as a diagnostic of successful crystal learning: period doubling
   indicates the model has entered the DTC phase and is learning
   in the crystal regime.

